author: Greg Miller
title: Traverse City West beats Cadillac to claim Big North Title
text:
Traverse City West beats Cadillac to claim Big North Title Posted: Follow @9and10sports 
CADILLAC - The Traverse City West Titans won a physical game on Tuesday night over Cadillac, 4-1. The win clinches the Big North Conference Championship for the Titans who are now 11-0 in conference play with one game remaining. 
Dalton Michael got the visitors on the board in the first half, scoring off of an Alex Gloshen assist. It would stay 1-0 into the second half when twin brother Donovan Michael would make it 2-0. 
Cadillac would cut the lead on a goal by Mike Gussert, but that was as close as the Vikings would get. Cody Miller and Donovan Michael added insurance goals late for the final tally. Most Popular Stories Most Popular Stories More>>
